link for STORED PROCEDURE HASH FILE : https://www.mssqltips.com/sqlservertip/4037/storing-passwords-in-a-secure-way-in-a-sql-server-database/
STORED PROCEDURE TO HASH THE PASSWORD FILE IN THE SERVER
    -> [dbo].[uspAddUser] : Add user in the database
        EXECUTION TO ADD USER IN THE DATABASE
        > DECLARE	@responseMessage nvarchar(250)
        EXEC dbo.uspAddUser
          @pLogin = 'keshavy@maqsoftware.com',
          @pPassword = '#1Password',
          @pFirstName = 'Keshav',
          @pLastName = 'Yadav',
          @responseMessage=@responseMessage OUTPUT
        SELECT	@responseMessage as 'Message'

    -> [dbo].[uspLogin] : authenticate the user in the database
        > DECLARE	@responseMessage nvarchar(250)
           EXEC	dbo.uspLogin
		   @pLoginName = ?,
		   @pPassword = ?,
		   @responseMessage = @responseMessage OUTPUT
           SELECT	@responseMessage as 'Message'
